# Intuition & Approach
- Explained in the code

# Code
```
class Solution
{
   	LOGIC

   	KARNA KYA HAIN❓
   	1. Integer "n" diya hain isko sum of "k positive integers" mein todna
   	hain.
   	2. k should always be ">=2".Matlab->Jyada se jyada numbers mein break karo.
   	3. Jo bhi k number ke sets banenge unme se max product wala set lena hain.

   	INTUITION &APPROACH
   	1. Ab apne ko itna to samajh aa raha hain ki "n ko bahut saare different
   	sets mein toda ja sakta hain".
   	2. Hame lekin max prod wala hi set lena hain.
   	3. So we have "many choices" to make sets.
   	4. Jahan yeh "choice shabd aagaya" wahan lagega "Recusion".
   	5. Ab Recurrence Relation❓
   	- Maximize karna hain to matlab har recursion mein "max" return karenge.
   	- Ab har num jo "<=n/2" hoga usse n ko break karenge .
   	- Why n/2❓Kyoki we have to make sure ki "jyada se jyada k value ho".
   	- Observation ke hisab se jitne jyada numbers mein breaked utna bada prod.
   	- Agar ">n/2" hoga to bade bade num mein break karna padega isse k ki val
   	choti ho jayegi.
   	- "BASE-CASE":n==1->return 1
   	- So loop lagega "1 to n/2" tak ka aur har i ke liye max nikalenge. So,
   	"res=max(res,i* Recursion(n-i))"
   	Where "Recursion(n-i)" means the max product for n-i value.
   	6. Ab kaafi overlapping problems hongi so to resolve this we will use DP.
   	7. RECURSION -> MEMOIZATION -> TABULATION
   	8. Memoization Steps❓
   	- See what parameter is changing decide the dp dimension .->Here only 1
   	param is changing so "1D array".
   	- In recurrence relation store the max val in dp[n]
   	- Check if any dp[x] has been previously solved.
   	9. Tabulation Steps
   	- Replace Recurrence function with dp[]
   	- Declare base case in dp array.
   	- The recursion loop will be replaced by for loop.
   	 "Meaning of dp[i]"❓-> It denotes the max product for digits in which
   	the num i is divided.
//==============================================================================================================================
    public:
         //MEMOIZATION    
        int Memoization(int n, vector<int> &dp)
        {
            if (n == 1) return 1;
           	//BASE CASE
            if (dp[n] != -1) return dp[n];
           	//Already solved
            int ans = n;
           	//Could be INT_MIN also
            for (int i = 1; i <= n / 2; i++)
            {
                ans = max(ans, i* Memoization(n - i, dp));
               	//Finding max among sets
            }
            return dp[n] = ans;
           	//Storing the max val
        }
    int integerBreak(int n)
    {
        if (n < 4) return n - 1;
       	//Precalculated
        vector<int> dp(n + 1, -1);
       	//As only one param is changing
        return Memoization(n, dp);
    }

   	//TABULATION
    int integerBreak(int n)
    {
        if (n < 4) return n - 1;
        vector<int> dp(n + 1, 0);
        dp[0] = 1;
        dp[1] = 1;
       	//BASE cases
        for (int num = 1; num <= n; num++)
        {
           	//Iterating for num 1 to n
            for (int div = 1; div <= num; div++)
           	//Calculating max prod for every num
            {
                dp[num] = max(dp[num], div *dp[num - div]);
            }
        }
        return dp[n];
    }
};
```
