dp[i] means maximum product of number i ( ignore k>=2 ). So dp[2]=2 and dp[3]=3 . When the product is max, n always break into 2 and 3. So for each n>=4 , the solution is `2*dp[n-2]` or `3*dp[n-3]`

```java
public int integerBreak(int n) {
	if(n<=3) return n-1;
	int[] dp=new int[n+1];
	dp[2]=2;
	dp[3]=3;
	for(int i=4;i<=n;++i){
		int i2=2*dp[i-2];
		int i3=3*dp[i-3];
		dp[i]=Math.max(i2,i3);
	}
	return dp[n];
}
```

