Just using several manual test cases to find that for any number the product will be max when it is consisting of sum of several small numbers (majorly 3). and this will be valid for all the number greater than 5 (n >= 5)


```
import java.util.*;
class Solution {
    public int integerBreak(int n) {
	//Taking exception cases
        if(n==2) return 1;
        if(n==3) return 2;
        if(n==4) return 4;
        int count3 = n/3;
        int rem = n%3;
		// remainder must not be 0 or 1 as it will decrease the resulting value
		// If remainder is 1 then we will be adding 1 3 from count3 
		//so count3 will be reduced by 1
		// and rem will increase to 4
		//if rem == 0 then set it to 1
        rem = (rem==1)?4:(rem==0)?1:2;
        count3 = (rem==4)?count3-1:count3;
        int ans = (int)Math.pow(3, count3) * rem;
        return ans;
    }
}

```

